data.title: ONElist Office
data.meta_description: Sam Rushing recently came across some old photos he took, including this one, which is a panorama of the old ONElist building in Redwood City. It was taken in February, 2000, which was after we merged with eGroups and before we were acquired by Yahoo (and became Yahoo Groups). The office was a converted warehouse and had about 50 people in it. This photo doesnâ€™t show all the cubicles behind the photographer, nor does it show the offices underneath.
